pair A, B, C, D, E, F, I;

A = (1,2);
B = (0,0);
C = (3,0);
I = incenter(A,B,C);
D = (I + reflect(B,C)*(I))/2;
E = (I + reflect(C,A)*(I))/2;
F = (I + reflect(A,B)*(I))/2;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(incircle(A,B,C));
draw(F--D--E);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$E$", E, NE);
label("$F$", F, NW);
[/asy]

solution:
First, we build a diagram:

[asy]
size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
pair B = (0,0), C = (3,0), A = (1.2,2), P = foot(A,B,C), Q = foot(B,A,C),H = intersectionpoint(B--Q,A--P);
