label("$P$",(5,0),S);
label("5",(0,0)--(5,0),S);
label("10",(0,0)--(5,8.6603),NW);
[/asy]

Then $\triangle ABP$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $AP=\sqrt{3}BP=5\sqrt{3}\text{ cm}.$ Thus, the height of the pile is $$5 + 5\sqrt{3} + 5 = \boxed{10 + 5\sqrt{3}}\text{ cm.}$$

problem:
Suppose that there are two congruent triangles $\triangle ABC$ and $\triangle ACD$ such that $AB = AC = AD,$ as shown in the following diagram. If $\angle BAC = 20^\circ,$ then what is $\angle BDC$? [asy]
